  "timeframe": "5m",
  "market_context": "NQ1! trending lower on the 5-minute chart with a clear sequence of expansion and shallow retracement phases. The analyst uses the hourly chart as the higher time frame bias and the 5-minute as the lower time frame for intraday execution, demonstrating the fractal nature of the model.",
  "key_observation": "Phases of price (expansion-retracement-expansion) apply fractally. A shallow retracement that fails to trade back into the prior range, combined with a bearish higher time frame closure and a change in state of delivery, signals the retracement phase has ended and a new bearish expansion is beginning.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Shift the bias framework down — use the hourly chart as the higher time frame and the 5-minute as the lower time frame, applying the fractal model.",
    "Step 2: Identify the prevailing trend on the 5-minute: price is trending down with repeated expansion-retracement-expansion sequences and shallow pullbacks.",
    "Step 3: Wait for the retracement phase to exhaust rather than chasing the expansion already in progress.",
    "Step 4: Confirm with a bearish higher time frame (hourly) closure aligning with a change in state of delivery on the 5-minute.",
    "Step 5: Evaluate whether price gives a reversal signature (expansion back into the prior low) or a continuation signature (shallow retracement failing to re-enter the range).",
    "Step 6: Observe the very shallow retracement, inability to trade back into the prior range, and a bearish closure — confirming continuation lower.",
    "Step 7: Enter on the continuation, anticipating the new expansion leg lower."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "The fractal model is time-frame agnostic — hourly bias paired with 5-minute execution works the same as daily/hourly. Align entries with the end of the retracement phase using HTF closure plus change in state of delivery, and let continuation signatures (shallow pullbacks failing to re-enter range) confirm the next expansion.",
